scoreProfile.message: Students read the text aloud to practice pronunciation. System will match the pronunciation with the text and do auto-marking. This helps to reduce teacher’s workload on marking. After system auto-marking, teacher can still amend the score manually.

scoreDesc.message: Currently, system auto-marking is restricted for 200 words only for reading aloud and audio within 2 minutes due technical restriction. Exceeding these two limits will cause failure in auto-marking! Please enter not more than 200 words into the read-aloud content column.

gradeRule.message: Student’s assignment result=All peer review’s average score – number of not-scored-yet assignment * 5% * total score of assignment, for example: For full mark of 100%, if a student gets his peer review score as 80, but he only reviews 1 out of 4 assignment assigned to him, 3 * 5% * 100 of score should be deducted. So the total result of the student will be :80 - 3 * 5% * 100 = 65 marks.

appealContent.message: Students can appeal to the teacher about the average score of the peer review assignments, and the teacher can change the average score of the peer review assignment, but student will still be deducted the score of the student for failing to finish peer reviewing in time.

stuAppealContent.message: When student is not happy with the average score, student can complain to his/her teacher and get the teacher to do marking. The final score will be teacher’s score – assignments to be evaluated *5%* total assignment score.
